# =============================================================================
# SAFE FILES TO REVIEW BEFORE COMMITTING
# =============================================================================

# These files MIGHT be safe but should be manually reviewed:
# - kdeglobals (global KDE settings)
# - kwinrc (window manager settings)
# - kglobalshortcutsrc (keyboard shortcuts - check for personal app paths)
# - plasma-org.kde.plasma.desktop-appletsrc (desktop layout - check for personal widgets)
# - plasmashellrc (panel configuration)
# - konsolerc (terminal settings - remove recent files section)
# - katerc (text editor settings)
# - systemsettingsrc (system settings UI preferences)
# - krunnerrc (application launcher settings)
# - Custom color schemes in ~/.local/share/color-schemes/
# - Custom Plasma themes in ~/.local/share/plasma/

# =============================================================================
# NOTES FOR MAINTAINERS
# =============================================================================

# Before committing any KDE config files:
# 1. Run: grep -r "$(whoami)" . (check for usernames)
# 2. Run: grep -r "$HOME" . (check for home paths)
# 3. Run: grep -r "Recent" . (check for recent files)
# 4. Run: grep -r "@.*\.com" . (check for email addresses)
# 5. Manually review plasma layout files for personal widgets
# 6. Remove any window geometry/position settings
# 7. Remove any file paths in konsole/kate configs

# Remember: When in doubt, DON'T commit it!
# It's better to have a minimal public config than expose personal data.
